<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-128-810  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 128 810.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Vision Graphics andamp; Image Processing  Jan 1990 v49 n1p68(17).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Octree generation from object silhouettes in perspective views.andO;(Note) (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Srivastava, Sanjay K.; Ahuja, Narendra.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>An approximate representation of the space taken up by objects inthe workspace suffices in many robotics applications, and thegeneration of one such representation, the octree is studied here.andO;The octree represents the space taken up by objects in theworkspace defined by a 'universe cube' that shows the octreerepresentation a single (root) node if it is empty (marked inwhite) or full (marked in black).andP;  The universe cube is decomposedinto eight octants represented by eight children of the root nodein any other case, and the root node is marked gray to showpartial occupancy of the workspace.andP;  Generation of the octree ofan object from its images is studied.andP;  The octree representationof the object is constructed given the silhouettes of perspectiveviews of an object taken from different directions.andP;  An algorithmis presented that accepts images taken from arbitrary viewpoints.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Object RecognitionImage ProcessingTheoretical ResearchThree-Dimensional GraphicsAlgorithm AnalysisNew TechniqueScene AnalysisTree StructuresOctree Encoding.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   A cube and its decomposition into octants. (chart)An object and its octree representation. (chart)Spiral and bisectrix used to decompose polygon into convexcomponents. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>